This repo contains implementation of PHP editor features (i.e. syntax highlighting, content assist, code validation) for Orion - my Google Summer of Code 2011 project. You can find both Orion plugins and server-side code here.

Directories info:

* orion-client-php-syntax-highlight-plugin - Orion plugin for syntax highlighting, totally client-side
* orion-client-php-content-assist-plugin - Orion plugin for content assist, communicates with server-side plugin
* orion-client-php-code-validation-plugin - Orion plugin for code validation, communicates with server-side plugin
* orion-server-php-plugin - server-side plugin (bundle) providing required functionality for client-side plugins

INSTALLING

To install PHP syntax highlighting in Orion:
1. Put contents of orion-client-php-syntax-highlight-plugin/web/ into public accessible dir
2. Symlink / move orion-client-php-syntax-highlight-plugin/web/css/default-theme.css in place of same file in org.eclipse.orion.client.core bundle in your Orion server installation
3. Install PhpSyntaxHighlight plugin in Orion using public accessible HTML link to orion-client-php-syntax-highlight-plugin/web/plugins/phpEditingPlugin.html
4. Orion will now open PHP files with syntax highlighting



For more information about the project, please visit following blog:

http://orion.gusak.eu/
